Uses of Package
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.control

Packages that use de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.control
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.bytecode Provides the classes for byte code instructions. 
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.general Provides abstract superclasses for the instruction classes. 
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.replaced.quick Provides QuickInstruction classes which can be used to speed up execution. 
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.replaced.replacer Provides ReplacingInstruction classes that can be used to set QuickInstruction classes. 
 

Classes in de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.control used by de.wwu.muggl.instructions.bytecode
JumpAlways
          Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will always lead to a jump in the control flow.
JumpConditional
          Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will lead to a jump in the control flow under a specified condition (if).
JumpException
          Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that can throw an exception which will disrupt the control flow.
JumpInvocation
          Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will invoke another method.
JumpNever
          Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will never lead to a jump in the control flow.
JumpSwitching
          Interface that is to be implemented by a switching operation (lookupswitch or tableswitch).
